# Class Management Backend

Backend for:
- JupyterLite teaching, in-class quizzes, and mock exams
- SEB-backed formal exams
- objective grading
- fill-gap grading
- AI-assisted essay grading with human review

## Structure

```text
backend/
  app/
    main.py
    core/
    models/
    schemas/
    api/
    services/
    workers/
  migrations/
  tests/
  
  
## Bulk roster import

Endpoint:
```bash id="2i7i7x"
POST /api/users/bulk-import
Payload:

{
  "users": [
    {
      "email": "student1@example.com",
      "full_name": "Student One",
      "matric_no": "MAT001",
      "role": "student"
    }
  ],
  "default_password": "welcome123",
  "skip_existing": true
}
Attendance

Create attendance session:

POST /api/courses/attendance/sessions

Mark attendance:

POST /api/courses/attendance/mark
Live attempt monitoring

List attempts for an assessment:

GET /api/admin/assessments/{assessment_id}/attempts

Live SEB session monitor:

GET /api/admin/assessments/{assessment_id}/live-monitor
AI grading worker

Run one job:

python -m app.workers.grading_jobs --job-id 1

Run pending jobs:

python -m app.workers.grading_jobs --pending --limit 20
Blueprint-based assessment assembly

This allows you to build an assessment from rules such as:

question type
difficulty
topic
count

Current implementation selects deterministic rows ordered by question id.
You can later upgrade it to random selection, weighted selection, or blueprint balancing.


---

# `backend/Makefile`  
Append this worker target.

```make id="3ni3j8"
worker:
	python -m app.workers.grading_jobs --pending --limit 20




## Question bank JSON import/export

Import:
```bash id="27q5xp"
POST /api/questions/import

Export:

GET /api/questions/export
Grade publication

Publish grades for an assessment:

POST /api/grading/assessments/{assessment_id}/publish

View gradebook:

GET /api/grading/assessments/{assessment_id}/gradebook

Student view of published grade:

GET /api/grading/my-grades/{assessment_id}
Attempt expiry auto-submit

Run expiry check:

python -m app.workers.grading_jobs --expiry-check

Run expiry check only for formal exams:

python -m app.workers.grading_jobs --expiry-check --assessment-type formal

